      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Main arguments for regulating AI to prevent existential risk include the concentration of powerful capabilities in unregulated hands, the speed at which AI safety failures could occur at scale, and the inability of current compliance frameworks to assess long-term alignment. Proponents emphasize that without proactive governance, autonomous systems may develop objectives misaligned with human values or outpace our ability to control their impact. Therefore, establishing robust policy becomes essential to ensure that advanced AI technologies remain safe, controllable, and beneficial for humanity.",
